<div id="review_2043956781" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2043956781" />
    <a title="BernLuvsBooks " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3087404-bernluvsbooks"><img alt="BernLuvsBooks " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1585010050p2/3087404.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2043956781?book_show_action=true">Oct 26, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="BernLuvsBooks " class="user" itemprop="url" name="BernLuvsBooks " href="/user/show/3087404-bernluvsbooks">BernLuvsBooks </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3087404-bernluvsbooks?shelf=2018">2018</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3087404-bernluvsbooks?shelf=adult-reads">adult-reads</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2043956781" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15546788808286934785">🔥 🏠 3.5 stars (rounded up). While beautifully written, emotional and intense - <b>
  <u>
    <i>Little Fires Everywhere</i>
  </u>
</b> didn&apos;t blow me away as much as I expected it would. It was a slow-burn book that required your investment and I have to admit to skimming some pages because they felt long. <br/><br/>The story for me was about more than the storyline though that was certainly interesting. <b>What resonated with me was Ng&apos;s depiction of relationships.</b> The relationships between mothers and their children, the rela</span>
  <span id="freeText15546788808286934785" style="display:none">🔥 🏠 3.5 stars (rounded up). While beautifully written, emotional and intense - <b>
  <u>
    <i>Little Fires Everywhere</i>
  </u>
</b> didn't blow me away as much as I expected it would. It was a slow-burn book that required your investment and I have to admit to skimming some pages because they felt long. <br /><br />The story for me was about more than the storyline though that was certainly interesting. <b>What resonated with me was Ng's depiction of relationships.</b> The relationships between mothers and their children, the relationships between friends, the relationships between siblings and the complicated relationships between family members. Ng powerfully explored these relationships and wasn't afraid to showcase how at times we seem to hurt those we love the most because of our own unhappiness, apprehension or feelings of inadequacy. <b>I loved how flawed and real the relationships were in this novel.</b> <br /><br />Another standout for me was the exploration of motherhood. In Elena Richardson and Mia Warren we see two polar opposite mothers. Elena very rigid, proper, opinionated and the epitome of success within her town. Mia with her bohemian lifestyle was in contrast artsy, free and openly loving. Their lives would intertwine when Mia and her daughter Pearl rent an apartment from the Richardson's. Pearl becomes smitten with the Richardson's children and their life. Izzy, the youngest Richardson child, in turn becomes smitten with Mia. Each child essentially finds something they are missing in the other family. For Mia it is an open acceptance, understanding and love. For Pearl who was an only child, always on the move - it is a house full of siblings with more things than they could ever need. <br /><br /><b>This is a story that unfolds as the lives of the characters unravel.</b> The characters were well written and complex. They all had layers to them, that were skillfully peeled away as Ng skillfully weaves her story. "Weaves" is the perfect word here as the story is connected by a host of characters and linked through many different relationships and actions. We see why they behave the way they do, we come to understand their actions even if they are wrong. <br /><br />Overall, this book was very definitely enjoyable. I wholeheartedly enjoyed the explorations into the characters. I was simply never wowed by it so while I enjoyed it, I didn't love it. I think the slowness of the book coupled with a busy week might not have been the best time to delve into such a slow burner but I am happy that I read it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15546788808286934785" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


